The paper deals with the complexity of ontology-mediated querying, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (AI) and databases (DB). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with description logic (DL), which is a subfield of logic (LO), and the complexity of queries, which is a topic in data structures (DS) and computational complexity (CC). Hence, cs.LO, cs.DS, and cs.CC are also likely sub-categories.
